WHO   — The Light Warriors — the four silent, player-named, player-classed heroes (from Fighter, Thief, Black Belt, Red/White/Black Mage) who each bear one darkened Orb and set out to restore the world's light
WHAT  — the four silent, player-named, player-classed heroes (from Fighter, Thief, Black Belt, Red/White/Black Mage) who each bear one darkened Orb and set out to restore the world's light
WHERE — FF1 · Final Fantasy — Square, Famicom 1987 / NES 1990  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy; the Light Warriors; the Orbs; Garland; Chaos  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — They are the blank slate the whole genre was projected onto: nameless and voiceless, a story you author rather than receive — the first Final Fantasy party.
HOW   — Crystallized from the original Final Fantasy (Square, 1987/1990).

